{% extends 'layouts/example.njk' %}

{% block audio %}
<chain-blam id="bus">
  <gain-blam gain="0.85"></gain-blam>
  <filter-blam type="highpass" id="highpass" freq="50" q="15"></filter-blam>
  <limiter-blam></limiter-blam>
  <analyser-blam id="analyser"></analyser-blam>
</chain-blam>
<pads-blam id="piano" gain="0.7" choke>
  <bank-blam>
    <sample-blam src="{{site.basedir}}/static/sounds/minimal/piano.mp3"></sample-blam>
  </bank-blam>
  <chain-blam out="bus">
    <reverb-blam mix="0.125">
      <sample-blam src="{{ site.basedir }}/static/sounds/IRs/stadium.mp3"></sample-blam>
    </reverb-blam>
    <filter-blam freq="1000">
      <blam-blam prop="freq" value="8000|8000|1000|750" from="sequencer-blam" chance="0.75" ramp="0.25"></blam-blam>
    </filter-blam>
  </chain-blam>
  <lfo-blam prop="detune" gain="66" beats="1">
    <blam-blam prop="beats" value="3|3|0.25|0.125|0.0625" from="sequencer-blam" chance="0.25" ramp="0.125" revert></blam-blam>
    <blam-blam prop="gain" value="50|50|25|100" from="sequencer-blam" chance="0.25" ramp="0.125" revert></blam-blam>
  </lfo-blam>
  <blam-blam id="killswitch" prop="gain" value="0" from="sequencer-blam" chance="0.333" revert></blam-blam>
</pads-blam>
<pads-blam id="kick" out="bus">
  <bank-blam>
    <sample-blam src="{{site.basedir}}/static/sounds/minimal/kick-01.mp3"></sample-blam>
    <sample-blam src="{{site.basedir}}/static/sounds/minimal/kick-02.mp3"></sample-blam>
    <sample-blam src="{{site.basedir}}/static/sounds/minimal/kick-03.mp3"></sample-blam>
  </bank-blam>
</pads-blam>
<pads-blam id="snare" out="bus">
  <bank-blam>
    <sample-blam src="{{site.basedir}}/static/sounds/minimal/snare-01.mp3"></sample-blam>
    <sample-blam src="{{site.basedir}}/static/sounds/minimal/snare-02.mp3"></sample-blam>
  </bank-blam>
  <blam-blam prop="detune" value="-400~400"></blam-blam>
  <blam-blam prop="length" value="1|1|1|0.25|0.125|0.05"></blam-blam>
</pads-blam>
<pads-blam id="tom">
  <bank-blam>
    <sample-blam src="{{site.basedir}}/static/sounds/minimal/tom.mp3"></sample-blam>
  </bank-blam>
  <chain-blam out="bus">
    <pan-blam pan="0">
      <blam-blam prop="pan" value="-1~1"></blam-blam>
    </pan-blam>
    <gain-blam gain="0.5">
      <lfo-blam prop="gain" gain="0.5" beats="0.001">
        <blam-blam prop="beats" value="0.00025~0.01"></blam-blam>
      </lfo-blam>
    </gain-blam>
  </chain-blam>
  <blam-blam prop="length" value="1|0.25|0.125"></blam-blam>
</pads-blam>
<pads-blam id="pluck" gain="1.5">
  <bank-blam>
    <sample-blam src="{{site.basedir}}/static/sounds/minimal/pluck-01.mp3"></sample-blam>
    <sample-blam src="{{site.basedir}}/static/sounds/minimal/pluck-02.mp3"></sample-blam>
    <sample-blam src="{{site.basedir}}/static/sounds/minimal/pluck-03.mp3"></sample-blam>
    <sample-blam src="{{site.basedir}}/static/sounds/minimal/pluck-04.mp3"></sample-blam>
    <sample-blam src="{{site.basedir}}/static/sounds/minimal/pluck-05.mp3"></sample-blam>
    <sample-blam src="{{site.basedir}}/static/sounds/minimal/pluck-06.mp3"></sample-blam>
    <sample-blam src="{{site.basedir}}/static/sounds/minimal/pluck-07.mp3"></sample-blam>
    <sample-blam src="{{site.basedir}}/static/sounds/minimal/pluck-08.mp3"></sample-blam>
  </bank-blam>
  <chain-blam out="bus">
    <filter-blam type="highpass" freq="500">
      <blam-blam prop="freq" value="100~1500"></blam-blam>
    </filter-blam>
    <echo-blam beats="0.666"></echo-blam>
    <reverb-blam mix="0.25">
      <sample-blam src="{{ site.basedir }}/static/sounds/IRs/plate.mp3"></sample-blam>
    </reverb-blam>
  </chain-blam>
</pads-blam>
<sequencer-blam bpm="90" id="transport" swing>
  <track-blam id="pianoTrack" to="#piano">
    <bar-blam s="1 0 0 0 0 0 0 0"></bar-blam>
    <repeat-blam x="6">
      <bar-blam s="0 0 0 0 0 0 0 0"></bar-blam>
    </repeat-blam>
    <bar-blam s="0 0 0 1 1 0 0 0" chance="0.3"></bar-blam>
  </track-blam>
  <track-blam class="drum" to="#kick" id="kickTrack" override="tomTrack">
    <bar-blam s="1 0 0 0 0 0 0 0"></bar-blam>
    <bar-blam s="0 0 0 0 0 0 2 0"></bar-blam>
    <bar-blam s="3 0 0 0 0 0 0 0"></bar-blam>
    <bar-blam chance="0.3" s="3 2 3 0 3 2 0 3"></bar-blam>
  </track-blam>
  <track-blam class="drum" to="#snare" override="tomTrack kickTrack">
    <bar-blam s="0 0 0 0 1 0 0 0"></bar-blam>
    <bar-blam s="0 0 1 2 1 0 0 2" chance="0.5"></bar-blam>
  </track-blam>
  <track-blam class="drum" to="#tom" id="tomTrack" chance="0.75">
    <bar-blam s="0 0 1 0 1 0 0 0 1 1"></bar-blam>
  </track-blam>
  <track-blam to="#pluck" chance="0.7">
    <repeat-blam x="4">
      <bar-blam s="0 0 0 0 0 0 0 0"></bar-blam>
    </repeat-blam>
    <bar-blam s="0 0 0 ? ? 0 0 0"></bar-blam>
    <bar-blam s="? 0 0 ? 0 0 ? ?"></bar-blam>
    <bar-blam s="? ? 0 0 ? 0 0 ?"></bar-blam>
    <bar-blam s="? ? ? ? 0 0 0 0"></bar-blam>
  </track-blam>
</sequencer-blam>
<tap-blam id="transport" to="sequencer-blam" prop="playPause">
  <button aria-pressed="false" class="u-round" aria-label="play">{% icon 'playPause' %}</button>
</tap-blam>
{% endblock %}

{% block dialog %}

{% renderTemplate "md" %}

There’s a lot going on here and I’m not going to explain it all. Instead, why not take a listen while you explore the source code? 

The first thing you might notice is the `<media-blam>` and `<audio>` elements are missing. And good riddance, frankly, because we can achieve a lot more with the `<pads-blam>` and `<notes-blam>` elements: true sample-based instruments.

Also, be sure to look inside `<sequencer-blam>` where I’ve written the composition (to be _rewritten_ with each play through). 

One last note on the original electric piano sample, now available via the `<pads-elem>` element with `id="piano"`: I’m always looking for new and better ways to emulate degraded tape. That wobbly, fluttery sound just does something to my Xennial brain. 
  
[Logic](https://support.apple.com/en-gb/guide/logicpro/lgcef18b8994/mac), [Helix](https://line6.com/support/topic/62459-retro-reel/), and other platforms all have their tape emulation plugins. Using **HYPERBLAM**, I’ve arrived at a pretty realistic and satisfying algorithm using a filter (`<filter-blam>`), an LFO controlling the `<pads-blam>`s `detune` property (which modulates pitch, creating a _vibrato_) and a couple of `<blam-blam>`s. 

```html
<chain-blam out="bus">
  ...
  <filter-blam freq="1000">
    <blam-blam prop="freq" value="8000|8000|1000|750" from="sequencer-blam" chance="0.75" ramp="0.25"></blam-blam>
  </filter-blam>
</chain-blam>
<lfo-blam prop="detune" gain="66" beats="1">
  <blam-blam prop="beats" value="1.5|1.5|0.25|0.125|0.0625" from="sequencer-blam" chance="0.5" revert></blam-blam>
</lfo-blam>
```

The first `<blam-blam>` randomizes the filter’s frequency value, using a `ramp` to interpolate between each successive frequency. This emulates _wear_: a tape will—unnevenly—lose the ability to reproduce higher frequencies over time. Another `<blam-blam>` controls the frequency (in `beats`) of the LFO attached to `detune`. This creates “flutters” in the pitch modulation, emulating the tape wheel slowing and speeding up in unexpected places.


